Rating: 4
great cheesecake! I used my graham cracker crust recipe from another cheesecake. I didn't use the caramel swirl - too much trouble and I like cheesecake standing alone on my plate. I drained the pumpkin like Ellie from Olympia said to do. I never realized pumpkin had so much water in it! The texture of the cheesecake came out exactly like I like it - firm. I don't like soft, cream-like cheesecake. I decorated the topping with orange sprinkles done in a pumpkin shape (I have small -1.5 inch- cookie cutters in fall shapes. Placed that it center and sprinkled orange sugars inside to shape the pumpkin, and green for the stem). It does need something as decoration, though.

