Rating: 4
Delicious and fairly easy. This cake has just the right amount and depth of pumpkin flavor to make cheesecake un-boring, while being more decadent than simple pumpkin pie. I made this for Thanksgiving AND Christmas dinner and everyone raved. If you do not care for gingersnaps, you can use regular butter piecrust (rolled thin, patted about 1.5" up the sides of the springform pan, and prebaked) or graham cracker/butter crumb crust. Both were very good in my variations. I would not bother with a water bath or slow cooling of the cake because the topping is going to conceal any cracks and there is no taste difference in a cracked vs "perfect" cheesecake.

Rating: 4
This was a very good cheesecake recipe and fairly simple as well. I made the following adjustemnts according to personal preferance: I used graham crackers in the crust because the gingersnaps usually end up getting soggy when I have made gingersnap crusts for cheesecakes in the past. I also, doubled the cinnamon, and added some nutmeg to the filling. I will definitely be making this recipe again!

Rating: 4
Incredible! This was the first cheesecake I ever made & it was not hard at all. I made it for Thanksgiving & everyone loved it. It was gone so fast. Do not hesitate to make this. My daughter in law does not like pumpkin anything & she loved it. Give this a try you won't be disappointed. By the way, the water bath method with foil wrapped around it worked best-no cracking, & after it was finished baking I turned off the oven & opened the door to let it cool for an hour to prevent any sinking -PERFECT!

Rating: 4
This is spectacular. I like a firmer cheesecake, and the water in the pumpkin takes away from that. To remove excess water from the pumpkin, line baking sheet with triple layer of paper towels. Spread pumpkin on paper towels in roughly even layer. Cover pumpkin with second triple layer of paper towels and press firmly until paper towels are saturated. Peel back top layer of towels and discard. Grasp bottom towels and fold pumpkin in half; peel back towels. Repeat and flip pumpkin onto baking sheet; discard towel.

