I have made this more times than any other single recipe that I can think of, as my father-in-law repeatedly requests it for thanksgiving or Christmas gatherings. Personally I am not a big fan of cheesecakes but this one might just win me over. I have done it with low-fat cream cheese as well as regular, and you really can't tell the difference. I do prefer the caramel on top, as long as it is sparing, but I don't think the sour cream adds much. I have done it with or without a water bath, but probably prefer to use one just as a "good luck" charm, although doing it without has turned out fine too. This was the first cheesecake I ever made, and I think it is pretty hard to go wrong, whatever you do.

