This is the first cheesecake I've made and it was a huge success (it was the only dessert to disappear after a huge Thanksgiving dinner). I made a couple of changes; One...I used a 10" springform pan (it was the perfect size, no leftover batter) & TWO...I added 2 Tbls finely chopped crytallized ginger to the crust. Otherwise I followed the recipe to the T (NO flour needed - it turned out real rich & creamy... just the way we like it). Don't skip the topping or the caramel either as it looks beautiful and tastes even better. I read the review that said store bought caramel isn't as good as homemade so I made Ina Garten's caramel recipe & I had some "Mrs Richardsons" caramel on hand; taste test side by side, almost no difference. I also followed the advice to pipe the caramel on by filling a small ziplock baggie & cutting the corner off (super easy, no mess!). I've already been asked to make this cheesecake again for Christmas. This recipe is a definite keeper!

