Rating: 4
I have made this twice in the last six weeks (once for Thanksgiving and once for Christmas) and it was much admired both times, but I liked it much better on one occasion than the other because of a key modification. One time I made it with the 2-4 Tbs of flour other reviewers have mentioned and once I made it without, and I would strongly, strongly recommend including the flour. I think I actually used close to 4 Tbs. The time I didn't include the flour, the cheesecake was too soft, even when I left it in the oven for an additional 30 minutes--it held up to slicing, but it was more like a mousse or pumpkin silk pie than the New York-style cheesecake that I like. I baked in a water bath both times, which seemed to ensure even baking. Other than that (flour and the water bath) I made it according to the recipe. I used Whole Foods Whole Treat caramel sauce one time, which was perfect, and Hersheys brand caramel sauce the other, which was thinner in consistency and not as good.

