Rating: 3
I agree with the last reviewer regarding adding a little flour - all "new york" cheesecakes seem to. Someone mentioned water leakage into crust. Here is a solution. Do check that the base and walls seem snug first (sorry), then always use two sheets of thick foil. It is best to place them flat on top of each other at 45 degrees , and get rid of wrinkles and pockets. Place unfilled pan on top and smooth foil up sides of pan tightly. Fold top edges over and try to press into pan with as little space between foil and pan ( to avoid steam getting in between) and avoid excess bulk (ditto). When I follow these rules, I never have soggy crusts. Hope it helps.

Rating: 3
