Made this for a dinner party. I modified this recipe quite a bit. First, for the crust: I used gingersnaps from Trader Joe's (saw this in another review - great suggestion!)and used at least two cups. Instead of toasted pecans, I used candied pecans also from Trader Joes. For the filling: I used probably two cups of pumpkin and added more spices such as: 1 tsp fresh ground nutmeg and 1/2 tsp of cloves. I skipped the whole caramel topping, but did use some sour cream to top it with some decorations I piped on. I also baked it in a water bath, which they don't mention here. Very important to keep refrigerated until about a hour before serving. Unfortunately, the hostess left it out the whole dinner and I felt it got a little too soft. But, still was very good texture and taste. I particularly loved the crust!

