Rating: 4
Yum! Yum! This cheesekcake has double appeal: people who don't like pumpkin pie often eat this right up, while pumpkin lovers really enjoy it too. To the previous cook concerned about water baths: the water bath is a cinch, just make sure you tightly wrap your pan in foil. However, if you have a convection option on your oven, you can get away with skipping the bath. Both ways help the cake to cook more evenly; it will still puff up and then drop; that's normal. The great thing about this cake is that you put a topping on and the cracks don't show! Good luck and enjoy!

