WOW!!! The best cheesecake recipe I have ever tried! It's so creamy, with just enough pumpkin flavor. The caramel swirl topping is beautiful, and really adds to the flavor. I disagree with the previous reviewers...the whipping cream added to the topping mixture is exactly right! Easily spreadable, and not too runny. This will be one of my standards...we may never have pumpkin pie again!

Rating: 3
Market didn't have gingersnaps so I settled for the standard graham cracker crust. It was still delicious with a creamy consistency, perfect balance of cheese and pumpkin, and it looked lovely. I made my own caramel sauce which was thick enough to create a beautiful swirl pattern on top, with enough to serve on the side. "Joy of Cooking" has a great recipe called "Caramel Sauce Cockaigne" that includes sugar, water, butter, heavy cream and vanilla. Not much cheesecake or caramel sauce left over from this years' Thanksgiving dinner!

Rating: 4
I added 1/2 cup more cream cheese to the 3/4 cup of cream cheese mixture reserved for the topping. I agree with other reviewers that 5 tablespoons of whipping cream would make the topping too runny. Just slowly add whipping cream a tablespoon at a time until you have a nice spreading consistency. The first time I made the cake I drizzled the caramel and it just ran into puddles instead of looking nice so I did not use it the second time. The dessert is rich enough to not need the additional caramel or sour cream toppings. I also baked it at 350 the first time and the ginger snap crust burned slightly. The second time I baked it at 325 and it needed about 10 additional minutes for the center to set but the crust was just right.

