Very, very good. I'm not a huge pumpkin fan or a huge cheesecake fan, but I liked this. And the pumpkin pie lovers, loved it. It was very easy to make, and the crust was fabulous!! I line the bottom of the springform pan w/ foil and folded the overhanging foil up around the sides of the pan. I had no problem w/ butter seepage. I also cooked at 325 for about 1hour and 20 min. I cooled it in the oven w/ the door propped open, and it didn't crack! Yea! I accidentally used all the whipping cream to make cinnamon whipped cream to serve w/ the cheesecake and didn't have any leftover for the topping. So, I heated the cream cheese mixture in the microwave for about a minute so it was spreadable like icing. I then added the caramel sauce (Smucker's) and swirled. It worked perfect. I served w/ the cinnamon whipped cream and drizzled caramel sauce over the entire plate. Yum!

