I have made this cheesecake every year since it first appeared in Bon Appetit. It has always received rave reviews and I have given the recipe out to many friends (who have also added it to their Thanksgiving menu every year). I suggest to cover the bottom of the pan with aluminum foil before baking. It stops all the butter from dripping out and causing smoke in the oven. Also I only put the crust on the bottom of the pan (not up the sides). I have found that it is hard to cut the crust at the point where it curves from the bottom up the sides. It gets very hard-- almost caramelized (but it still tastes delicious). I have mine baking in the oven right now for Thanksgiving!

