Rating: 4
I have made this cheesecake to "guest" at many holiday feasts. I have made a couple of alterations that seem to take this from good to WOW! For a deeper taste, I substitute  cup of baked yam (pureed) for  cup of the pumpkin and use brown sugar for part of the 1 2/3 cup sugar. I also add one tsp of vanilla paste and  tsp ginger to the filling. I prefer the contrast of 1 cup sour cream, 1 Tbsp sugar, and 1-2 Tbsp of bourbon with a little finely grated orange rind as a baked topping (the last 5 minutes of baking time). Generously drizzle caramel topping over the top of the cake. I know, I know, it is almost a completely new recipe. Nevertheless, I have yet to bring home any leftover dessert!

